text: ## [](#programming-language-ts--rust)Programming Language: TS + Rust

title: Hybrid AI Search 3 - The Full Tech Stack
text: There is no doubt that TS(JS) is already the first language for front-end development. The key is how to choose a back-end development language, With the help of AI, learning and using a language is not difficult, What matters is how to develop efficiently. To achieve efficient development, you need to be familiar with the common frameworks, compilation tools, testing tools, deployment tools, and

title: Hybrid AI Search 3 - The Full Tech Stack
text: tools, and deployment platforms of the corresponding programming languages. Although many problems are not difficult, they all take up our precious time. **Our precious time should be spent on the most important things.**

title: Hybrid AI Search 3 - The Full Tech Stack
text:
As a backend developer with 10 years of programming experience, who has deeply used C++, Java, Python, and Node, and has used Python to develop AI backend API for a year, **I decided to use TS for backend development to keep the front-end and back-end languages ​​consistent.**

**For the few scenarios that do require high performance computing, I would use Rust.**

title: Hybrid AI Search 3 - The Full Tech Stack
text: So you will find that the main language of the [MemFree](https://github.com/memfreeme/memfree) memfree project is TS, but the embedding sub-project that requires high-performance computing uses Rust

title: Hybrid AI Search 3 - The Full Tech Stack
text:
## [](#tp-database-upstash-redis)TP DataBase: Upstash Redis

I have tried many databases, and the reason why I finally chose Upstash Redis is:

*   Fast
*   ServerLess
*   Easy-to-Use
*   Cost-Effective

title: Hybrid AI Search 3 - The Full Tech Stack
text:
## [](#vector-database-lancedb)Vector DataBase: LanceDB

I have tried many databases, and also built a vectorized search service based on Faiss index. the reason why I finally chose LanceDB is:

*   High-Performance Column Store
*   Native vector Support
*   Native Lake Support
*   Native Serverless
*   Ease of Use and Maintenance
*   Written in Rust and High Performance

## [](#object-storage-cloudflare-r2--aws-s3-express)Object Storage: Cloudflare R2 + AWS S3 Express

Cloudflare R2 is cheap but fast, AWS S3 Express is fast but expensive.

So if you want to store some images, files, you could use Cloudflare R2, if you want to store database files, you should use AWS S3 Express

[SearXNG](https://github.com/searxng/searxng) is cheap but slow and need to slef-host, [Serper](https://serper.dev/) is fast but expensive.

You could refer to [MemFree](https://github.com/memfreeme/memfree) Mixed use
